
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Aesthetic Components of Management Ethics
AU  - Brady, F. Neil
Y1  - 1986/04/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1986.4283118
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1986.4283118
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 337
EP  - 344
VL  - 11
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Traditionally, the place of ethics in business practices has been to supply a decision procedure or some formal normative orientation. This paper asserts that the role of ethics is much larger than that, going beyond ?knowing that? to include ?knowing how? as an important epistemological extension to traditional ethical theory. Ethics thus becomes, in part, a form of art, giving added credibility to the commonly heard phrase ?the art of managing.?
AB  - Traditionally, the place of ethics in business practices has been to supply a decision procedure or some formal normative orientation. This paper asserts that the role of ethics is much larger than that, going beyond ?knowing that? to include ?knowing how? as an important epistemological extension to traditional ethical theory. Ethics thus becomes, in part, a form of art, giving added credibility to the commonly heard phrase ?the art of managing.?
