TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Female Entrepreneur: A Career Development Perspective
AU  - Bowen, Donald D.
AU  - Hisrich, Robert D.
Y1  - 1986/04/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1986.4283366
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1986.4283366
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 393
EP  - 407
VL  - 11
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Recent literature on female entrepreneurs and entrepreneurial careers reveals that: (a) up to this time, piecemeal studies of entrepreneurs (male and female) fail to provide a clear picture of the factors which encourage an individual to enter upon an entrepreneurial career; and (b) even less is known about female than male entrepreneurs. A comprehensive career model (a more definitive picture of the determinants of entrepreneurial behavior for women) is developed.
AB  - Recent literature on female entrepreneurs and entrepreneurial careers reveals that: (a) up to this time, piecemeal studies of entrepreneurs (male and female) fail to provide a clear picture of the factors which encourage an individual to enter upon an entrepreneurial career; and (b) even less is known about female than male entrepreneurs. A comprehensive career model (a more definitive picture of the determinants of entrepreneurial behavior for women) is developed.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1986.4283366
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1986.4283366
